SP.P:
It is not possible to reckon up all the Cases in which a Mistress may injure a Ser∣vant; tis true, and there can no Rule be set so exact, as that no Body shall be oppress'd: But I have two Things to say;
1. All the Injustice that can be suppos'd to happen that Way, is not equal to that which Mistresses and Families now suffer from the Insolence and Baseness of Ser∣vants; and therefore the Remedy is to be be and the letter Evil chosen.
2. There may be methods directed by the Law, that in such Cases where Mistresses have nothing Capital to charge upon a Servant, they shall be obliged to give them Certificates of their Behaviour.
